GitHub Desktop (GUI) Workflow:
=============================
(1) Clone repo

From GitHub Desktop: File → Clone Repository or use the clone URL.

(2) Create a new branch

Top panel → Current Branch → New Branch.

Make changes to code

Edit files locally in your code editor.

Stage the changes

GitHub Desktop detects changes.

Use the + button to stage selected files.

Commit with message

Enter a message like [JIRA-1234] Fixed XYZ → Click Commit to [branch name].

Push the changes

Click Publish branch (if first time), or Push origin (if already published).

Create Pull Request (PR)

Go to GitHub web UI → Navigate to the branch → Click “Compare & pull request”.

Add reviewers, test details

Enter test details, reviewers, and PR description → Click Create pull request.

Merge after review

Once approved → Click Merge Pull Request → Optionally delete branch.

